Investors Should Choose to Help Greece, Rehn Tells Kauppalehti

-- B y   K a t i   P o h j a n p a l o
-- 
2011-10-21T05:26:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-21/investors-should-choose-to-help-greece-rehn-tells-kauppalehti.html
European Union Economic and Monetary
Affairs Commissioner  Olli Rehn  said any private sector
involvement in the second Greek bailout should be voluntary,
Finnish business daily Kauppalehti reported today.  “The best option in the Commission’s view is a voluntary,
and above all controlled, arrangement,” Rehn told the Helsinki-
based newspaper. “In the summer we said  Greece ’s debt
sustainability is on knife’s edge. Now, it’s gone worse by most
measures.”  Click here for web link in Finnish  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
